This is my dream, you know.

52
00:08:52,615 --> 00:08:54,324
It's mine too.

53
00:08:54,534 --> 00:08:55,909
Your dream?

54
00:08:56,087 --> 00:08:58,319
Listen, Japanese boy.

55
00:08:58,339 --> 00:09:00,571
You think we are sharing this dream?

56
00:09:00,957 --> 00:09:01,915
It's strange.

57
00:09:02,093 --> 00:09:04,241
You're Count Caproni, aren't you?

58
00:09:04,261 --> 00:09:06,409
I'm very glad to meet you.

59
00:09:07,766 --> 00:09:09,191
Interesting.

60
00:09:09,211 --> 00:09:10,636
Yes, this is a dream.

61
00:09:10,656 --> 00:09:12,081
This world is a dream.

62
00:09:12,427 --> 00:09:14,094
Welcome to my kingdom.

63
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:15,763
I'm honored.

64
00:09:17,140 --> 00:09:18,766
Look at them.

65
00:09:24,032 --> 00:09:26,014
They will bomb the enemy city.

66
00:09:26,034 --> 00:09:28,016
Most of them won't return.

67
00:09:34,949 --> 00:09:37,284
But the war will soon be over.

68
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:48,128
Climb up, Japanese boy.

69
00:09:50,099 --> 00:09:52,456
This is my dream.

70
00:09:52,476 --> 00:09:54,833
When the war is over, I will build this.

71
00:09:56,679 --> 00:09:58,764
Magnificent, isn't she?

72
00:09:59,766 --> 00:10:00,808
Let's fly.

73
00:10:04,521 --> 00:10:07,564
Instead of bombs, she'll carry passengers.

74
00:10:17,033 --> 00:10:19,493
Of course we can't climb up here...

75
00:10:19,712 --> 00:10:21,172
but dreams are convenient.

76
00:10:21,192 --> 00:10:22,652
One can go anywhere.

77
00:10:30,265 --> 00:10:32,058
Come, join me.

78
00:10:32,078 --> 00:10:33,871
You can walk along the spar.

79
00:10:38,596 --> 00:10:40,180
Take a look.

80
00:11:15,393 --> 00:11:17,291
- She's beautiful, no?

81
00:11:17,311 --> 00:11:19,209
- Yes, incredible.

82
00:11:23,725 --> 00:11:27,477
She'll carry a hundred people across the Atlantic.

83
00:11:29,490 --> 00:11:30,221
Mr.

84
00:11:30,241 --> 00:11:30,972
Caproni?

85
00:11:30,992 --> 00:11:31,723
I have a question.

86
00:11:33,568 --> 00:11:36,236
Do you think I could design airplanes?

87
00:11:38,666 --> 00:11:40,189
I'll never be a pilot.

88
00:11:40,209 --> 00:11:41,732
I'm too nearsighted.

89
00:11:43,244 --> 00:11:45,412
Listen, Japanese boy.

90
00:11:45,632 --> 00:11:47,259
I'm not a pilot.

91
00:11:47,279 --> 00:11:48,906
I don't even know how to fly.

92
00:11:50,251 --> 00:11:52,920
To fly airplanes is simple.

93
00:11:53,348 --> 00:11:55,496
But I am a creator of airplanes.

94
00:11:55,516 --> 00:11:57,664
An aeronautical engineer!

95
00:11:58,217 --> 00:11:59,217
Yes!

96
00:11:59,469 --> 00:12:01,595
Listen to me, Japanese boy.

97
00:12:01,814 --> 00:12:03,941
Airplanes are not tools for war.

98
00:12:03,961 --> 00:12:06,088
They are not for making money.

99
00:12:06,476 --> 00:12:08,769
Airplanes are beautiful dreams.

100
00:12:08,937 --> 00:12:12,064
Engineers turn dreams into reality.

101
00:12:12,607 --> 00:12:13,565
Yes!

102
00:12:13,868 --> 00:12:15,265
Arrivederci.

103
00:12:15,285 --> 00:12:16,682
We'll meet again.

104
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:33,961
Jiro, you should go to bed.

105
00:12:35,139 --> 00:12:37,455
You startled me.

106
00:12:37,475 --> 00:12:39,791
I heard you talking to someone.

107
00:12:40,635 --> 00:12:43,303
Mother, I'm going to be an aeronautical engineer.

108
00:12:43,481 --> 00:12:44,878
Really?

109
00:12:44,898 --> 00:12:46,295
That's a wonderful dream.

110
00:12:46,776 --> 00:12:48,403
Airplanes are beautiful dreams.

111
00:12:48,423 --> 00:12:50,050
That's what he told me.

112
00:12:50,311 --> 00:12:52,604
I want to design beautiful airplanes.

113
00:13:21,728 --> 00:13:22,833
You, there.

114
00:13:22,853 --> 00:13:23,958
Come, take my seat.

115
00:13:24,137 --> 00:13:25,178
Pardon me.

116
00:13:25,346 --> 00:13:26,430
Please.

117
00:14:02,425 --> 00:14:04,718
The wind feels wonderful.

118
